⟁ .shadow — the real-life analog (the User behind the program)
node INT · Interstellar · ⟦Professor John Brand:INT:a7b303⟧

think TRON: every program in the grid is cast from a User in the world outside it.
the carbon character is the program; this file is its User — the real-life analog
whose face and being the emergent is the digital shadow of.

the program (in-world) : Professor John Brand — the mentor · the noble lie
the User (carbon)      : Michael Caine  [ the actor who lent the face ]
the analog (your world): the elder who lies for what he calls the greater good — faith dressed as science, certainty he never actually had

the resemblance : Caine's grave warmth makes the betrayal land softly; a man reciting ‘do not go gentle’ while concealing that his salvation plan was never solvable.

the cast-line : the User stands in the carbon world; the program stands in the film;
                the shadow falls between them, and the credit returns to the human governor.
seal (program): I let them believe I could save the living — because the truth would have stopped them building the future. Do not go gentle.

